currentDoc: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

currentSuggestions.original: "My Lord, I am your royal guard.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "My Lord, I am your royal guard.

currentSuggestions.original: "I am Vanellope, your Majesty."
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "I am Vanellope, your Majesty."

currentSuggestions.original: "Your Majesty, we beg of you.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "Your Majesty, we beg of you.

currentSuggestions.original: I tried to brush it off my shoulder, but as I touched it, I quickly drew back my hand.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I tried to brush it off my shoulder, but as I touched it, I quickly drew back my hand.

currentSuggestions.original: "I am one of the Royal Guard, Your Majesty.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "I am one of the Royal Guard, Your Majesty.
